        <span id="ChapterQuoteAudio">
        “I know with the help and strength I get from Heavenly Father that I can do hard.” 
        </span>
        <div id="ChapterText" class="clearfix">
            <!--span id="ChapterByline">
            <span id="textspanlichapter22">ELLIS LI</span><br /><span id="textspanlichapter24">DAUGHTER</span>
            </span-->

            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText"></span>I've been asked to talk about a favorite thought or phrase that I've had in my lifetime experience that meant a great deal to me and helped me in many ways. 
<br />
            </span>

            <!--div id="ChapterPictureGallery" class="clearfix">
                <ol class="GalleryPics">
                    
                </ol>    
            </div-->


            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                   We live in a troubled world. We have difficult times. We have spiritually-wrenching times in our lives when we need spiritual help. I know that we can't do things alone. We have to have help from our Heavenly Father with His Spirit to strengthen us and help bolster our faith. The one phrase that means the most to me is, “I can do hard.” 
            </span>
            
            <span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory1-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory1');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>

            <div id="restofstory1" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    I first heard those words when Marian's sister Carmel mentioned it. I don't remember what the circumstances were, but my son Marlon told me that she was talking to her daughters. Her daughters were commenting about something very difficult for them to do, and they didn't think they could do it. Carmel looked at them and said, “We can do hard. You can do this. I know you can because we can do hard.” <br /><br />

                    After Marlon told me about that and I heard those words, they seemed to go deep into my heart. They mean a great deal to me. They've helped me do some hard things. I keep that phrase on my shelf in my office and I look at it every day. It helps to get me through the days, because I know with the help and strength I get from Heavenly Father that I can do hard, and I try.
                </span>

